The paper deals with algorithms for testing properties of matrices, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of non-adaptive queries and the focus on matrix rank suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category. The use of query complexity and the focus on numerical properties suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also likely categories. The use of algorithms and the focus on testing suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also possible categories.
